OL,4,Ctackle lack of carers in South West
OL,6,FDr Andy Virr, from Cornwall Council,
OL,7,Fsaid: "It's particularly useful for
OL,8,Fpeople maybe with learning
OL,9,Fdisabilities, or autism, maybe elderly
OL,10,For dementia who, who probably need a
OL,11,Fbit more of a one to one support.
OL,13,F"And so it's an alternative to
OL,14,Fproviding care in someone's home as
OL,15,Fthey come and live in your home, and
OL,16,Fthat you have an opportunity to help
OL,17,Fthem to live as independently as
OL,18,Fpossible, maybe helping them to cook,
OL,19,Fmaybe help them to seek employment.
